channel.description:
I think the version of the pickaxe Jagex made looks ridiculous [url=http://img.techpowerup.org/090910/Capture018.png][click here to see it][/url], so I kinda redid some of it to look more like a proper pickaxe, made of dragon.

This is fit to HD characters unfortunately, I'll move it up for 317 characters just for you guys though. Give me a few minutes. But here;

Equip model: [url=http://uppit.com/v/1XJF5TLR]http://uppit.com/v/1XJF5TLR[/url]
Drop model: [url=http://uppit.com/v/1QL8BXUK]http://uppit.com/v/1QL8BXUK[/url]

I made my own drop model and ints and rotations.

ItemDef.java FOR MY BASE
[code]			case 15259:
				itemDef.actionData(1, "Wield");
				itemDef.models(48471, 48470, 48470, -1, -1);
				itemDef.modelData(1180, 700, 1100, 0, 0);
				itemDef.itemData("Dragon pickaxe", "Used for mining.");
				break;[/code]

or if you don't use a switch statement:

[code]			if(i == 15259) {
				itemDef.actionData(1, "Wield");
				itemDef.models(48471, 48470, 48470, -1, -1);
				itemDef.modelData(1180, 700, 1100, 0, 0);
				itemDef.itemData("Dragon pickaxe", "Used for mining.");
			}[/code]

Methods for renamed(you don't need if you use my base)
[code]	public void actionData(int a, String b) {
		actions = new String[5];
		actions[a] = b;
	}
	public void totalColors(int total) {
		originalModelColors = new int[total];
		modifiedModelColors = new int[total];
	}
	public void colors(int id, int original, int modified) {
		originalModelColors[id] = original;
		modifiedModelColors[id] = modified;
	}
	public void itemData(String n, String d) {
		name = n;
		description = d.getBytes();
	}
	public void models(int mID, int mE, int fE, int mE2, int fE2) {
		modelID = mID;
		maleEquip1 = mE;
		femaleEquip1 = fE;
		maleEquip2 = mE2;
		femaleEquip2 = fE2;
	}
	public void modelData(int mZ, int mR1, int mR2, int mO1, int mO2) {
		modelZoom = mZ;
		modelRotation1 = mR1;
		modelRotation2 = mR2;
		modelOffset1 = mO1;
		modelOffset2 = mO2;
	}[/code]

